snippet: A 911 dispatcher failed for several minutes to see an incoming report about a Manhattan crash that killed a 4-year-old girl, fire officials said.
abstract: New York City fire officials report that emergency medical workers were delayed in responding to car crash in Manhattan that left 4-year-old girl Ariel Russo dead because 911 dispatcher failed to see incoming report on computer screen for several minutes; officials vigorously dispute any suggestion that delay reflects wider problem in city's new 911 system.

byline.original: By MARC SANTORA and NATE SCHWEBER

lead_paragraph: A 911 dispatcher failed for several minutes to see an incoming report about a Manhattan crash that killed a 4-year-old girl, fire officials said.

headline.seo: Officials Admit Human Error in Delayed Response to Fatal Crash
headline.main: 911 Worker’s Error Delayed Response to Crash That Killed Girl, Officials Say
headline.print_headline: 911 Worker’s Error Delayed Response to Crash That Killed Girl, Officials Say
